// Semantic direction:
// minne_profiler tracks all memory allocations to help developers find leaks and reduce usage.
// allokerings_stakkspor captures the call stack at each allocation for source attribution.
// allokerings_levetid is the duration from allokering to frigjøring — long-lived unexpected objects signal leaks.
// heap_snapshot is a point-in-time capture of all live objects, their sizes, and reference graph.
// retensjons_tre shows which objects are keeping others alive, with retensjon_størrelse as total retained bytes.
// retensjon_grunn is the root reference (global, stack, finalizer) preventing collection.
// heap_sammenligning diffs two snapshots to find diff_voksende_typer that accumulate across operations.
// kandidat_lekkasje is an allocation site whose live_allokeringer grow monotonically across GC cycles.
// gc_runde_overlevelse counts how many GC cycles an object has survived; abnormally high = possible leak.
// flamme_graf_minne visualizes memory attribution as a flame chart — wider nodes allocate more bytes.
// størrelse_histogram buckets objects by størrelse to identify unexpectedly large instances.
// alders_histogram shows the age distribution; a spike in old ages suggests unexpected retention.
// sampling_profiler records allokerings_stakkspor at sampling_rate to reduce overhead.
// allokeringsgrad is allocations per second; high rates stress the young generation GC.
// smaps_les parses /proc/self/smaps (Linux) to show kernel-level memory region breakdown.
// tre_kart_vis renders the heap as nested rectangles proportional to objekt_størrelse.
// sanntids_oppdatering refreshes the vis at a configurable interval while the program runs.

// Primitive flow:
// heap_snapshot: pause GC -> traverser alle roter -> BFS gjennom objekt_feltpekere
//   for hvert objekt: oppføring{id, type, størrelse, feltpekere} -> lagre snapshot
// diff: sammenlign snapshot[N] mot snapshot[N-1]
//   diff_nye_objekter = objekter i N men ikke N-1
//   diff_voksende_typer = typer der total_størrelse er større i N
// lekkasje_analyse: for hvert allokeringssted: plot live_allokeringer over GC-runder
//   monoton vekst? -> kandidat_lekkasje(sannsynlighet=høy)
//   retensjons_tre: finn korteste sti fra rot til kandidat -> lekkasje_grunn
// flamme_graf: for hvert allokerings_stakkspor: akkumuler størrelse per stakkramme
//   render som SVG: bredde proporsjonal med bytes_allokert

// This defines the memory profiler: allocation tracking with stack traces, heap snapshots
// with retention trees, leak detection via monotonic growth analysis, flame graphs, histograms,
// and live heap visualization.
